==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pentad
<hw>Pen"tad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>penta`s</grk> <grk>penta`dos</grk>, a body of five, fr.
<grk>pe`nte</grk> five.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any element,
atom, or radical, having a valence of five, or which can be combined
with, substituted for, or compared with, five atoms of hydrogen or other
monad; <as>as, nitrogen is a <ex>pentad</ex> in the ammonium
compounds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any grouping of five things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentad</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pentad
<hw>Pen"tad</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having the
valence of a pentad.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentadactyle</ent>⟦br⟧
